#------------------
# Overview
#------------------
Setups the goods costs of various actions, units, etc.

Buildings:
A building has a construction_demand defined, which links to an entry here. Additionally, a building may have a entry in the possible_production_methods scope that links to an entry here too.

Units:
A unit has a maintenance_demand and construction_demand defined, which links to an entry here.

Special Construction:
A hardcoded action, such as remove_government_reform, has a goods demand of the same name here.

#------------------
# Entry
#------------------
<key< = {
    <goods> = <float>   # The goods amount for this demand. Can have multiple.
    
    <goods> = {
        <value> = <float>
        
        <effects>
    }
    # The goods scope can be accessed and more granular handling of the amount can be configured.
    
    category = <type>   # The category of this demand. From common/goods_demand_category/
    
    hidden = yes>       # Whether this demand is hidden from the interface.
}